# Fas 4 STEG 2 (F4-2) + STEG 9 (F4-9) — local NLP-tier data assets (Swedish + English).
#
# The sv_SE DSSO Hunspell dictionary is an UNMODIFIED LGPL-3.0 data file shipped
# verbatim (BUILD §3.1 copyleft separation); the en_US Hunspell dictionary is an
# UNMODIFIED permissive SCOWL/Ispell-BSD data file (F4-9). swedish.stop / english.stop
# are embedded byte-identical to PostgreSQL 18.3's built-in lists (stopword parity,
# ADR 0074). The repo default is core.autocrlf=true; these files MUST keep their exact
# LF bytes through commit/checkout, or the SHA-256 integrity pin in
# DssoDictionaryIntegrityTests breaks, the "unmodified" guarantee is voided, and the
# to_tsvector('english') parity diff drifts. -text disables all EOL conversion for them.
*.dic -text
*.aff -text
src/Jobbliggaren.Infrastructure/TextAnalysis/swedish.stop -text
src/Jobbliggaren.Infrastructure/TextAnalysis/english.stop -text

# Shell hooks must keep LF endings (repo default is core.autocrlf=true). A CRLF `\r`
# breaks bash `case`/`[[ ]]`/`read` matching in the worktree-reaper/session-end hooks
# (issue #673) — pin them so checkout never converts to CRLF.
.claude/hooks/*.sh text eol=lf
